  "texts": [
    "Our analysis encompassed claims across both voting records and OECD datasets, with performance measured against human-annotated verdicts.",
    "The baseline GPT-4o Naive model performed poorly on both case studies, suggesting that the model's internal knowledge alone is insufficient for accurate fact verification.",
    "When we excluded cases where our system failed to retrieve relevant evidence (w/o Irrelevant), we observed substantial improvements in accuracy: an increase of 13.1 percentage points for voting-related claims and 21.5 percentage points for OECD-related claims.",
    "This improvement demonstrates the critical role of successful evidence retrieval in fact verification accuracy.",
    "Detailed examples of the system's reasoning and explanations can be found in Appendix D.1."
  ],
